description: The Enforcement Directorate has filed a chargesheet against Sonia Gandhi, Rahul Gandhi, and others in the National Herald money laundering case, alleging proceeds of crime worth Rs 5,000 crore. A special court has scheduled a hearing for April 25 to consider the chargesheet, marking a significant development in the case.
title: ED files chargesheet against Sonia, Rahul in Herald case

description: Robert Vadra, husband of Congress leader Priyanka Gandhi, faced six hours of questioning by the Enforcement Directorate regarding a 2008 land deal involving his company, Skylight Hospitality. The ED is investigating the deal where Skylight bought land for Rs 7.5 crore and sold it to DLF for Rs 58 crore shortly after.
title: ED questions Vadra in Haryana land deal case

description: Thousands of Muslim pilgrims face disappointment as 42,000 applicants are unable to perform Haj this year, prompting calls for PM Modi's intervention. The minority affairs ministry attributes the issue to delays by private tour operators, while operators cite problems with the Saudi portal's payment system.
title: Pilgrims appeal to PM as 42k can't make it for Haj

description: India is expected to receive above-normal southwest monsoon rainfall this year, according to the IMD's forecast. This is crucial for agriculture, boosting Kharif crops and the rural economy. While some regions may experience below-normal rainfall, most of the country, including the monsoon core zone, is likely to receive ample precipitation, potentially exceeding 91 cm.
title: IMD predicts ‘above normal’ rainfall in India this monsoon

description: In Raipur, a 13-year-old boy has been detained by police for allegedly raping a three-year-old girl, who is now in critical condition and receiving intensive care. The incident occurred when the boy lured the toddler, a neighbor, to an isolated location while her parents were napping.
title: 13-year-old boy held for raping toddler in Chandigarh

description: Tamil Nadu Chief Minister M.K. Stalin has formed a high-level committee, led by retired Justice Kurian Joseph, to address concerns about state autonomy and federalism. The committee will recommend measures to protect states' rights and improve Centre-state relations, with reports expected in the coming years.
title: Amid Centre run-ins, Tamil Nadu sets up panel to 'shield' states' rights

description: The Assam government has mandated the use of Assamese in all official communication alongside English, effective Tuesday. This directive, aimed at preserving Assamese identity, is part of implementing Clause VI of the Assam Accord. Bengali and Bodo will also be used in Barak Valley and the Bodo Autonomous Region, respectively, with English.
title: Assam makes Assamese must in all official work

description: India's first ATM on a train successfully completed its trial run on the Panchavati Express between Manmad and Mumbai. Railways officials reported smooth operation, with minor signal disruptions in no-network zones. This collaboration between the Bhusawal division and Bank of Maharashtra allows passengers to withdraw cash and access banking services while traveling, potentially extending to other major trains if popular.
title: Fast cash express: Train ATM brings banking services on track

description: Guru Ghasidas Central University in Chhattisgarh is investigating allegations that a programme officer forced students to offer namaz during an NSS camp held in Shivtaraiin. Students claim they were threatened with certificate withholding for protesting the 'forced namaz'. Police have requested details from the university as part of their inquiry into the complaint.
title: Forced to offer namaz: Chandigarh university students

description: A special court has instructed Lokayukta police to proceed with their investigation into the Mysore Urban Development Authority (Muda) alternative site allotment scam, following protest petitions. The court has asked the police to submit a conclusive final report by May 7, 2025. This order comes after a preliminary report had cleared CM Siddaramaiah and others.
title: Lokayukta gets court nod to continue Muda 'scam' probe

description: Dan Caldwell, a senior adviser to US defense secretary Pete Hegseth, has been placed on administrative leave following an investigation into leaks at the Department of Defense. Caldwell was identified as the source of an "unauthorized disclosure" involving sensitive communications and national security information. The investigation is ongoing, separate from recent firings within the department since Hegseth assumed leadership.
title: Pentagon leak probe: Pete Hegseth’s top adviser Dan Caldwell placed on leave
Arrest warrants against Bangladesh former PM Sheikh Hasina, son & 16 others
Bangladesh halts yarn imports from India through land ports

description: Google is set to streamline the search experience by redirecting country-specific domain names to its primary domain, google.com, in the coming months. This change, announced on April 15th, will not affect search functionality or legal obligations. Google states that country-level domains are no longer necessary as they have been providing localized results since 2017.
title: Google Search website URL is changing globally: What it means for Google users

description: Ashtam Premsagar, a 40-year-old Indian migrant worker from Telangana, was fatally stabbed in Dubai on April 11 after a workplace argument with a Pakistani colleague. Premsagar, a father of two who had not yet met his younger daughter, was supporting his family.
title: Pakistani man stabs to death Indian migrant in Dubai
Prank gone wrong: 4 arrested for staging fake crime scene
Gurugram horror: Air hostess sexually assaulted while on ventilator in ICU

description: Salesforce CEO Marc Benioff credits his 1996-97 India trip to meet Guru Mata Amritanandamayi in Kerala as the genesis of Salesforce. During the visit, while explaining his vision, Mata Amritanandamayi emphasized the importance of giving back. This profoundly influenced Benioff, shaping Salesforce's philanthropic ethos and his personal belief in being kind to others.
title: Salesforce CEO remembers 'life lesson' that his Indian Guru taught him

description: Security forces initiated a large-scale combing operation in Surankote's Lasana village, Poonch district, following a brief exchange of fire with terrorists on Monday night. Additional troops have been deployed to prevent the terrorists from escaping as search operations continue. This follows the recent killing of three Jaish-e-Mohammad terrorists in Kishtwar and the death of a JCO in Keri Bhattal area.
title: Searches launched in J&K’s Poonch after brief firefight with terrorists

description: Chief Minister Omar Abdullah urges the central government to restore statehood to Jammu and Kashmir, six months after assuming office. Following a meeting with Union Home Minister Amit Shah, Abdullah expressed optimism about the restoration. The National Conference government passed a resolution advocating for statehood, viewing it as a crucial step towards healing and reclaiming constitutional rights.
title: Six months in office, Omar says ‘right time’ to restore J&K statehood

description: NBA icon Stephen Curry is set to launch *Shot Ready* this fall, a photo book offering an intimate glimpse into his life and career. Published in partnership with Random House, the book features over 100 never-before-seen photographs. Curry shares his philosophy on preparation, growth, and mindfulness, aiming to inspire readers.
title: Stephen Curry reveals never-before-seen photos in his new book 'Shot Ready'

description: The NIA has charged three individuals, including a Pakistan-based handler, in a terror conspiracy linked to arms seizures in J&K's Poonch. Abdul Aziz, Munawar Hussain, and Nazir Hussain face charges under UAPA and the Arms Act. Nazir, an operative of Jammu and Kashmir Ghaznavi Force, allegedly radicalized youth and supplied arms for terror attacks.
title: Terror conspiracy: NIA files chargesheet against Pakistani handler, 2 others

description: During an antitrust trial, Mark Zuckerberg admitted Facebook acquired Instagram due to its superior camera product, supporting the FTC's claim that Meta strategically bought rivals. Zuckerberg conceded Meta often failed to develop successful apps internally. The FTC argues these acquisitions stifled competition and innovation, seeking to unwind Meta's deals for Instagram and WhatsApp.
title: Zuckerberg admits FB bought Instagram because of this ‘better’ feature

description: As US immigration policies evolve, Indian students face increasing challenges when aiming to study in the country. With rising visa rejections, stricter regulations, and heightened scrutiny over personal activities, the path to higher education in the US has become more complex. Key changes include visa revocations without notice, potential cancellation of the OPT program, and stricter visa renewal processes, making it essential for students to stay informed and prepared.
title: 10 warning signs for Indian students and professionals eyeing US

description: US-China relations face a potential breakdown. Attention shifts to India as a possible replacement. China directs airlines to halt Boeing orders. This move aims to boost domestic aircraft manufacturing. The US President's tariff policies face criticism. Experts question if the US has overplayed its hand. India is seen as a potential beneficiary of the trade war.
title: As US-China ties crash and burn, eyes turn towards India

description: Amidst escalating trade tensions, Donald Trump asserts that "the ball is in China's court," highlighting the tariff war where US tariffs on Chinese goods have reached 145%. Trump emphasizes that China needs a deal with the US, as they desire access to the American consumer market and its financial resources.
title: 'Ball is in their court on tariffs': White House says Trump open to a deal with China

description: The ICC has lauded the selection of Fairgrounds in Pomona, Southern California, as the venue for cricket at the Los Angeles 2028 Olympics, marking the sport's return after 128 years. ICC Chair Jay Shah expressed enthusiasm for collaborating with the IOC to ensure cricket's success.
title: Cricket in Olympics: ICC welcomes LA28 venue announcement
Gajab Swad Ba! Japan’s envoy takes a bite of Bihar’s soul – litti-chokha

description: Ajinkya Rahane shouldered the blame after Kolkata Knight Riders' shocking collapse against Punjab Kings, despite being comfortably placed to chase 112. KKR lost seven wickets for just 24 runs in six overs, turning a seemingly assured victory into a historic defeat. Rahane emphasized the need for batsmen to take responsibility and remain positive for the remaining half of the tournament.
title: 'I take the blame': Ajinkya Rahane after KKR's shocking defeat

description: A court in Budgam, J&K, has ordered Hizbul Mujahideen chief Syed Salahuddin to appear within a month regarding a 2002 murder and arms case. Failing to comply, proceedings will commence to declare him a proclaimed offender. The court noted that Salahuddin is reportedly residing in Pakistan-Occupied Kashmir, making his arrest impossible, and ordered public notification of the proclamation.
title: J&K court issues proclaimed offender notice against Hizbul chief

description: Punjab Kings achieved a historic feat by defending a meager total of 111 against Kolkata Knight Riders, securing a 16-run victory in a stunning turnaround at Mullanpur. Yuzvendra Chahal's exceptional bowling, with figures of 4 for 28, dismantled KKR's batting lineup, while Marco Jansen's early strikes further contributed to the collapse.
title: Record Alert! Punjab Kings defend lowest-ever total in IPL history

description: In a tragic incident in Samba district, Jammu and Kashmir, a 25-year-old Territorial Army jawan, Ram Chandra Choudhary, was electrocuted on Monday. The incident occurred near Bari Brahmana station when he climbed atop a passenger train and came into contact with a high-tension wire.
title: Territorial Army jawan electrocuted after climbing atop train in J&K’s Samba

description: The Supreme Court's ruling on Tamil Nadu bills and governor's assent timelines is celebrated by opposition parties as a victory for federalism. The court emphasized governors must act on the advice of ministers and cannot indefinitely delay bills. While strengthening state autonomy, some experts caution about potential imbalances in the federal structure, suggesting a need for constitutional discipline.
title: TN vs guv: 'SC verdict may create imbalance in federal structure'

description: Harvard University faces financial challenges as the Trump administration froze over $2.2 billion in federal funding, prompting demands to alter DEI programs and admissions policies. Despite a substantial endowment, the university relies on federal grants for research and student aid, leading to a hiring freeze and reassessment of capital projects.
title: Trump cancels Harvard funding: Here's how much the university receives from US govt

description: Xavier Bartlett made a promising IPL debut for Punjab Kings, taking a wicket in his first over against KKR. Despite PBKS's batting struggles, Bartlett contributed with the bat after his impressive performance in the Big Bash League, where he was the leading wicket-taker. His recent international success, including multiple wickets, highlights his potential impact for Punjab Kings this season.
title: Who is Xavier Bartlett? PBKS' new pace sensation dismisses de Kock

description: WWE NXT's April 15th edition promises high-stakes action, setting the stage for NXT Stand & Deliver 2025. Ethan Page, Eddy Thorpe, Wes Lee, and Lexis King will clash for a shot at Ricky Saints' North American Championship. A Tag Team Gauntlet match will determine Fraxiom's next challengers, featuring Briggs & Inamura and others.
title: WWE NXT: Full match card, show highlights, how to watch, and more

description: Punjab Kings pulled off a stunning victory against Kolkata Knight Riders in Mullanpur, defending a low score of 111. KKR's chase faltered dramatically thanks to Yuzvendra Chahal's game-changing spell of 4 for 28. Despite an early partnership by PBKS openers, KKR bowlers Harshit Rana, Varun Chakravarthy, and Sunil Narine restricted them.
title: Yuzvendra Chahal battles shoulder injury to help PBKS beat KKR

description: Leaked screenshots have ignited excitement for The Elder Scrolls 4: Oblivion Remastered, suggesting significant graphical improvements over the 2006 original. While Bethesda remains silent, the images found on Virtuous' website seemingly confirm the remake's existence. Rumors point to a possible April release, with a Deluxe Edition potentially offering bonus content.
title: The Elder Scrolls 4: Oblivion Remastered is real, with release coming soon

description: S. Jaishankar criticized Pakistan's role in promoting terrorism, highlighting their double-dealing in Afghanistan and persistent "bad habits." He emphasized that the 2008 Mumbai attacks marked a turning point in India-Pakistan relations, signaling a shift in India's tolerance. Jaishankar also linked national progress to the strength and quality of a nation's universities.
title: 26/11 Mumbai attack turning point between India-Pak ties: Jaishankar

description: India's government has firmly dismissed Pakistan's criticism of the Waqf Amendment Act as unfounded and biased, asserting that Pakistan lacks the authority to comment on India's internal affairs. The external affairs ministry highlighted Pakistan's poor treatment of minorities and advised them to address their own issues instead of lecturing others.
title: 'Baseless & motivated': India snubs Pakistan's remark on new Waqf law

description: Lauren Sánchez's Blue Origin flight highlighted a new era for women in space, addressing the historical challenge of ill-fitting spacesuits. Collaborating with designers, Sánchez championed suits tailored for women, moving away from traditionally male-centric designs.
title: How Jeff Bezos' fiancée Lauren Sánchez solved NASA's 'uniform problem'

description: Trinamool Congress MP Saket Gokhale strongly criticized Uttar Pradesh CM Yogi Adityanath's remarks on the Murshidabad violence, urging him to address the unrest in his own state. Gokhale cited the Agra incident involving a mob attack on a Rajya Sabha MP's residence.
title: 'Laaton ke bhoot': Yogi lambasts Mamata over Murshidabad violence; TMC hits back

description: Alan Wilkins, the veteran commentator, joyfully announced his recovery from throat cancer and his imminent return to India for the IPL season. Overcoming this health challenge, the 71-year-old broadcaster expressed immense gratitude and a renewed sense of youthfulness. His return to the commentary box is celebrated by fans, marking a triumphant moment in his distinguished career.
title: 'Never give up': Alan Wilkins heads to IPL after being cleared of cancer

description: Arbaaz Khan and Sshura Khan's recent visit to a maternity clinic in Mumbai has sparked pregnancy rumors. The couple, who married in December 2023, were seen together, with Arbaaz protectively escorting Sshura. This comes after their intimate wedding and Arbaaz's statements about finding fulfillment in his second marriage, with his son Arhaan sharing a warm bond with Sshura.
title: Sshura Khan spotted visiting maternity hospital with husband Arbaaz Khan

description: Sunil Narine achieved a significant milestone in the IPL, becoming the bowler with the most wickets against a single franchise, surpassing Umesh Yadav's record. Narine's crucial spell of 2 for 14 against Punjab Kings helped KKR dismantle their opponents for a mere 111. KKR's dominant bowling performance, led by Harshit Rana and supported by Varun Chakaravarthy, secured a comprehensive victory.
title: Sunil Narine creates IPL history with most wickets against a single team

description: A video of Hardik Pandya gifting Kashvee Gautam a bat went viral. The video got over 80 million views on Instagram. Pandya promised Kashvee a custom-made bat after learning she idolised him. He fulfilled his promise before Mumbai Indians' match. Kashvee recently earned her first call-up to the Indian women's team. She performed well in the WPL 2025.
title: 80M views & counting! Kashvee's video with Hardik breaks the internet

description: Following violent clashes in Murshidabad, West Bengal, triggered by protests against the Waqf (Amendment) Act, displaced families recount harrowing experiences of destruction and fear. Homes and businesses were attacked, leaving several dead and hundreds homeless, now seeking refuge in relief camps. Security forces have been deployed, and investigations are underway to restore peace and provide support to the affected communities.
title: 'Attacked us, set everything on fire': Survivors recall Murshidabad horror

description: Bloach rebels hijacked Pakistan's Jaffar Express last month. They used US weapons. These weapons were left in Afghanistan in 2021. The BLA attacked the train in Balochistan. The train was traveling to Peshawar. Security forces launched a rescue operation. Twenty-one passengers died in the attack. The terrorists contacted supporters in Afghanistan. Separatists want a greater share of Balochistan's resources.
title: Baloch rebels used US weapons to hijack Pakistan's Jaffar Express: Report

description: Assam has mandated Assamese as the compulsory official language for all government communications, including notifications and orders, as announced by chief minister Himanta Biswa Sarma. Bengali and Bodo will be used in the BTR and Barak Valley districts, respectively. English will remain for communication with the central government, but in case of interpretation differences, the English version will prevail.
title: CM Himanta declares Assamese compulsory official language for govt works

description: A Bengaluru Special Court has deferred its order on the ED's petition challenging the Lokayukta police's clean chit to CM Siddaramaiah in the MUDA site allotment case. The court awaits the Lokayukta's final report before ruling on the ED's challenge, which alleges the police overlooked key evidence.
title: Court defers order on ED petition in MUDA case against Siddaramaiah

description: Following public concern over alleged cracks on Patna's newly inaugurated JP Ganga Path, Bihar officials clarified that the observed gaps are expansion joints designed for weather-induced movements, not structural flaws. Minister Nitin Nabin assured the public that the bridge is safe, with no structural cracks present, and the joints were refilled after filler material dislodged due to traffic.
title: 'Cracks' on Rs 3,831 crore JP Ganga Path in Bihar sparks concern; officials respond

description: Hackers targeted crosswalk systems in California's tech hubs, replacing audio prompts with AI-generated voices mocking Elon Musk and Mark Zuckerberg. The compromised crosswalks in Palo Alto, Menlo Park, and Redwood City broadcast satirical messages, prompting officials to temporarily disable the voice announcement feature while investigating the breach that affected 12 crosswalks.
title: Crosswalks hacked in America to make fun of Elon Musk and Mark Zuckerberg

description: Immigration attorney Nicole Micheroni mistakenly received a DHS email ordering her to "self-deport immediately," sparking concern and confusion. The incident, linked to the CBP One app and its role in migrant parole, prompted DHS to acknowledge the error. Micheroni used the situation to educate the public about immigration parole and the importance of seeking legal counsel.
title: DHS responds after US citizen Nicole Micheroni gets 'Self-Deport' email from CBP

description: The entertainment world is buzzing with news as Ranveer Allahbadia faces cyber officials in Mumbai over controversial content. Meanwhile, Nadia Khan criticizes Hania Aamir's career choices amidst 'Sardaar Ji 3' rumors. Urvashi Rautela's cryptic social media post sparks a potential feud with Tamannaah Bhatia, and Randeep Hooda reflects on past film rejections due to his ego.
title: From Ranveer Allahbadia to Urvashi Rautela : Top 5 entertainment news of the day

description: MS Dhoni's explosive 26 off 11 balls propelled Chennai Super Kings to a thrilling victory over Lucknow Super Giants, reigniting his finisher persona. Harbhajan Singh lauded Dhoni's captaincy, stating it revitalised his batting and tactical acumen. Dhoni also achieved a milestone, becoming the first IPL player to complete 200 dismissals, further solidifying his legendary status.
title: 'He became captain & everything changed': Bhajji calls Dhoni 'Baahubali'

description: Indian stock markets rebounded strongly after a long weekend. The NSE Nifty 50 index rose significantly in Mumbai. India has recovered losses from US tariffs. It is seen as a safe haven amid global market uncertainty. Strong domestic growth supports this. India may benefit from supply chain shifts away from China.
title: India leads global recovery, first in world to erase Trump tariff losses

description: India and the United States are commencing discussions this week for a Bilateral Trade Agreement, starting virtually before an in-person meeting in May. This follows Prime Minister Modi and President Trump's agreement to strengthen ties, aiming to finalize the trade deal by fall. Both nations seek to expand bilateral trade to $500 billion by 2030.
title: India, US to begin talks on trade agreement this week

description: India's retail inflation hit a near six-year low of 3.34% in March, fueled by cheaper vegetables and protein-rich foods. This drop follows a recent repo rate cut by the RBI, which forecasts a 4% average CPI inflation for fiscal year 2025-26. Wholesale price inflation also decreased to a six-month low of 2.05%, driven by lower vegetable and essential food prices.
title: India's retail inflation logs 3.34% in March 2025, nearly 6-year low

description: Karnataka's rising star, R Smaran, has earned his first IPL call-up, joining Sunrisers Hyderabad as a replacement for the injured Adam Zampa. The 21-year-old left-handed batsman, celebrated for his impressive performances across formats last season, aims to learn from experienced players like Heinrich Klaasen and Pat Cummins. Smaran is eager to contribute and absorb knowledge from the team's seasoned lineup.
title: IPL 2025: R Smaran excited about Sunrisers Hyderabad call-up
JD Vance says it's 'absurd' of Zelenskyy to accuse US of taking Russia's side

description: Disagreement has emerged between BJP and JD(U) after Haryana CM's remark on Bihar Assembly polls. JD(U) leaders asserted Nitish Kumar as CM for the next five years, dismissing concerns of BJP outsmarting Nitish. Deputy CM Samrat Chaudhary affirmed Nitish Kumar would retain his post. Meanwhile, Congress and RJD convened to strategize an alliance, discussing seat-sharing and poll strategy.
title: JD(U) stands firm on Nitish, BJP stays vague on CM choice

description: Since taking office in 2019, Bukele has disbanded checks and balances like they were Black Friday leftovers. Judges? Fired. Opposition? Mocked. Constitution? “More like a suggestion,” he said, running for a second term despite an explicit ban. And yet, his approval ratings hover between 85–90%. To many Salvadorans, the tradeoff—liberty for safety—feels worth it.
title: Move aside Musk: Meet Trump's new BFF

description: Following Chennai Super Kings' much-needed victory against Lucknow Super Giants, concerns arose as MS Dhoni was seen limping, sparking worries about his fitness. This adds to CSK's challenges, already struggling at the bottom of the IPL 2025 table. Dhoni, who recently resumed captaincy, also emphasized the need for improved pitches at Chepauk to boost the batters' confidence.
title: MS Dhoni limping after CSK win - viral footage raises alarm bells

description: The Enforcement Directorate (ED) has filed a chargesheet against Congress leaders Sonia Gandhi and Rahul Gandhi concerning the National Herald case. This action follows the ED's recent initiation of proceedings to seize properties valued at over Rs 700 crore belonging to the Associated Journals Limited (AJL), a company with ties to both leaders.
title: National Herald case: ED charges Rahul, Sonia; Cong terms it 'state-sponsored crime'

description: Ayatollah Ali Khamenei expressed cautious optimism regarding nuclear talks with the US, acknowledging effective initial stages while maintaining skepticism. He advised against over-reliance on the talks' outcome. Despite Trump's frustration over slow progress and warnings of potential airstrikes, Iran insists the next round will occur in Oman, amidst escalating nuclear program concerns.
title: 'Neither optimistic nor pessimistic': Khamenei on nuclear talks with US

description: Rohit Sharma's underwhelming performance at the start of IPL 2025 is impacting the Mumbai Indians' campaign, according to Anjum Chopra. With MI struggling and Rohit's low scores leading to an "Impact Player" role, Chopra suggests a change in batting order might alleviate pressure and reignite his form, despite acknowledging his proven match-winning capabilities.
title: 'Not a crime to be out of form, but ...': Ex-cricketer on Rohit Sharma

description: Telangana CM Revanth Reddy addressed the "forest encroachment" controversy, accusing the opposition of spreading propaganda using AI regarding the HCU land allegations. PM Modi criticized the Congress government for attempting to "bulldoze forests," prompting a strong rebuttal from the Congress, highlighting Modi's own record on environmental clearances and tree felling.
title: 'Poisonous campaign': Telangana CM Reddy snubs 'forest razing' charge

description: Taylor Swift and Kanye West's feud reignites as West makes explicit posts about Swift, including disturbing sexual remarks. This comes after Swift revealed the trauma caused by West and Kim Kardashian's edited phone call release in 2016, which she says damaged her career. Travis Kelce is reportedly upset and wants to confront West, while Swift's fans have defended her online.
title: Taylor Swift opened up about the emotional damage from Kanye West and Kim Kardashian feud in 2023

description: Chinese factories are leveraging TikTok to sell directly to American consumers, bypassing retail markups and tariffs on luxury goods. Viral videos showcase alleged factory-direct alternatives to brands like Lululemon and Louis Vuitton, sparking debate about authenticity and pricing. While luxury brands deny Chinese manufacturing, experts warn of counterfeit operations capitalizing on tariff confusion to flood Western markets with fake goods.
title: TikTok in US brings 'alive' the 'Chinese nightmare' of Birkin

description: The Enforcement Directorate has filed a chargesheet against Congress leaders Sonia and Rahul Gandhi in the National Herald case, prompting a sharp reaction from the party, which called it a "state-sponsored crime." In other news, Assam has made Assamese the compulsory official language for government work, while India leads global market recovery after rebounding from Trump's tariff shock.
title: Top 5 news of the day

description: Donald Trump accused China and Vietnam of conspiring to undermine the United States following Xi Jinping's visit to Hanoi, where he met with Vietnamese President To Lam and signed 45 cooperation agreements. Trump claimed President Biden had lost trillions in trade to China but expressed a continued liking for Xi.
title: Trump dismisses Xi Jinping’s Vietnam tour as effort to ‘screw’ US

description: US President Donald Trump regards Prime Minister Narendra Modi as a friend, according to US State Department spokesperson Margaret MacLeod. She highlighted the "joint interests" between India and the US, emphasizing collaboration on counter-terrorism, advanced technologies, and increased business opportunities.
title: 'Trump sees Modi as friend': US official on relations with India

description: Donald Trump has threatened Harvard University's tax-exempt status, accusing it of promoting "terrorist inspired/supporting 'Sickness?'" after the university refused to comply with federal directives, leading to a freeze of $2.2 billion in grants and $60 million in contracts.
title: Trump targets Harvard's tax exempt status as varsity refuses to back down

description: The Mumbai Cricket Association (MCA) has decided to honour cricketing legends by naming stands at the Wankhede Stadium after Rohit Sharma, Ajit Wadekar, and Sharad Pawar. Additionally, a lounge will be named after former MCA president Amol Kale. The MCA also announced an increase in the corpus for affiliated clubs, aiming to bolster grassroots cricket infrastructure in Mumbai.
title: Wankhede stands to be named after Rohit Sharma, Wadekar and Pawar

description: Chennai Super Kings defeated Lucknow Super Giants in a recent IPL match. After the match, Rishabh Pant and MS Dhoni engaged in a lighthearted conversation. Dhoni discussed his spectacular run out of Abdul Samad. Zaheer Khan was also seen mimicking Dhoni's underarm action. Pant jokingly expressed his fear of being run out by Dhoni.
title: 'Wicket dekha, maar diya': Dhoni on his 'no-look' run-out. Watch
Waqf protests: Rijiju accuses CM Mamata of inciting violence

description: A woman was caught on CCTV assaulting a toll booth operator at the Chhijarsi Toll Plaza in Hapur after her FASTag showed insufficient balance. The woman slapped and attempted to strangle the attendant, while two men accompanying her misbehaved with staff. Police have registered a case and are working to locate the woman involved in the incident.
title: Fast and furious: Woman slaps toll worker 7 times in 4 seconds

description: India aims for a beneficial bilateral trade agreement with the United States, following the finalization of terms for the initial phase. Both nations seek to elevate bilateral trade to $500 billion by 2030, targeting completion of the first phase by year-end. Trade liberalization will address both tariff and non-tariff barriers.
title: 'Hope to negotiate good bilateral trade with US': India amid tariff tensions

description: The India Meteorological Department forecasts above-normal rainfall for India during the June-to-September monsoon season, estimating 105% of the long-period average. El Nino conditions, typically linked to reduced rainfall, are not expected. This prediction is vital for India's agriculture, which supports a significant portion of the population and contributes substantially to the GDP.
title: India to experience above-normal rainfall this monsoon, says IMD

description: Vipraj Nigam's journey from an 8-year-old with a dream to an IPL sensation is a testament to unwavering family support and serendipitous talent discovery. His father, Vijay, despite a challenging government job posting, fueled his son's cricketing aspirations, while his mother and grandfather made daily sacrifices, traveling long distances to support his training. Now, his wickets of cricket giants like Kohli and Rohit in the IPL highlight a remarkable rise, proving that dedication and unexpected turns can shape an extraordinary career.
title: Vipraj Nigam, the accidental spinner who's turning heads in IPL

description: The Supreme Court has cautioned judges against making inappropriate remarks in sexual violence cases, specifically addressing comments made by the Allahabad High Court that blamed a woman for inviting the alleged rape. This follows the Supreme Court's intervention in another Allahabad High Court case where the court diminished the severity of sexual assault against a child.
title: 'One has to be careful': SC on HC's rape victim ‘invited trouble’ remark

description: The Trump administration's proposed federal funding freeze raises concerns about its impact on universities, especially elite institutions like Harvard. While many universities may struggle, Harvard’s substantial endowment and diverse revenue streams provide resilience against such disruptions. With federal funding accounting for a small percentage of its overall revenue, Harvard is well-equipped to handle a freeze. Legal challenges are delaying the freeze’s implementation, but Harvard's financial strength ensures its research and operations remain stable despite external funding uncertainties.
title: Will Trump's funding freeze truly impact Harvard University?

description: Following the recent violence in Murshidabad, West Bengal, initial probes suggest possible involvement of Bangladeshi miscreants. The MHA is coordinating with state authorities to maintain peace and considering enhanced border security. Over 200 arrests have been made and 11 FIRs registered after demonstrations against the waqf law led to three deaths.
title: Murshidabad violence: Initial probe flags role of suspected Bangladeshi miscreants

description: Amid trade tensions with the US, China has reportedly instructed its airlines to halt further Boeing aircraft deliveries and U.S. parts purchases following retaliatory tariffs. This move puts Boeing in a precarious position within a crucial market, where China is projected to represent 20% of global aircraft demand.
title: China orders halt to Boeing jet deliveries as trade war with US intensifies

description: Uttar Pradesh CM Yogi Adityanath criticized West Bengal CM Mamata Banerjee for her alleged inaction regarding the Murshidabad violence, accusing her of enabling rioters under the guise of secularism. He also attacked Congress and Samajwadi Party for their silence on the issue, deeming them a burden on India.
title: 'Laaton ke bhoot': Yogi lambasts Mamata over Murshidabad violence

description: New USCIS guidelines have sparked confusion among Indian visa holders, but primarily affect undocumented individuals. Non-resident Indians with valid visas, including workers, students, and visitors, are generally not impacted.
title: Why most non-immigrant visa holders need not panic about new US registration rule

description: Indian stock markets saw a big jump. This happened after US President Trump paused some tariffs. The Sensex and Nifty both rose significantly. Investors feel more confident because of this change. India is also seen as a safe place to invest. Some sectors like auto and banking did well. People are watching to see what Trump does next with tariffs.
title: Investors gain Rs 18.42 lakh cr in 2 days: Reasons behind market rally

description: Scientists warn of an impending "Great Himalayan Earthquake," potentially exceeding magnitude 8, posing a significant threat to northern India due to accumulated tectonic pressure. With 59% of India vulnerable to seismic activity, experts emphasize the urgent need for preparedness.
title: Is the Great Himalayan earthquake to happen soon?

description: Comedian Vir Das has publicly criticized Air India for a disappointing travel experience. Despite paying a premium for their Delhi flight, he and his wife, recovering from a foot fracture, encountered broken amenities and a lack of assistance.
title: 'Delayed, not denied': Air India on Vir Das's wheelchair claim

description: Harvard University is in conflict with the Trump administration, which froze $2.2 billion in federal grants due to ideological disagreements. Harvard refuses to comply with demands to alter admissions policies and eliminate DEI programs, citing academic freedom. While facing financial strain and legal challenges, Harvard is standing firm against what it views as governmental overreach.
title: Why Harvard's $53.2 billion endowment may not save it from Trump

description: The Trump administration froze over $2.3 billion in federal funding to Harvard University, citing non-compliance with demands to address antisemitism and ideological bias. Harvard rejected these demands, deeming them politically motivated and an infringement on academic freedom. This action is part of a broader campaign targeting elite universities, aiming to reshape higher education and combat perceived left-leaning ideologies.
title: Harvard university's $2.2 billion funding frozen: What triggered Trump admin’s move?

description: Indian stock markets began the week positively, with Sensex surging over 1300 points and Nifty50 also at high, marking a positive opening for the week. Optimism was fueled by potential US trade concessions and positive global cues. Investors are also awaiting corporate earnings reports, while Asian markets generally saw gains, reflecting a positive international market sentiment.
title: Market opens in green, Sensex jumps over 1,500 points; Nifty near 23,307

description: A significant measles outbreak is alarming the United States, with over 700 confirmed cases after its elimination in 2000. The CDC is actively involved in containment, addressing the resurgence attributed to declining vaccination rates. Measles, a highly contagious airborne virus, poses a threat even to vaccinated individuals, though breakthrough infections remain consistent with previous years.
title: Measles makes a comeback in US, 700 confirmed cases so far: Safety tips

description: Chennai Super Kings broke their five-match losing streak in a thrilling victory, with MS Dhoni and Shivam Dube leading the charge. Dube's resilient innings, especially his explosive 19th over, secured the much-needed win. Dhoni acknowledged the team's struggles and hoped this victory would boost morale. The left-handed batter later shared insights into his approach, emphasising adaptability and composure.
title: MS Dhoni breaks silence, says 'God makes it very tough'

description: Chennai Super Kings defeated Lucknow Super Giants by five wickets, ending their five-game losing streak. CSK's bowlers set the stage, restricting LSG to 166/7, while Dhoni and Dube's explosive batting sealed the victory. Dhoni's reunion with LSG owner Sanjiv Goenka added a nostalgic touch to the win. After the game, Dhoni was seen sharing a light-hearted chat with LSG owner Sanjiv Goenka—a reunion of sorts, as Goenka also owned the now-defunct Rising Pune Super Giant franchise where Dhoni played for two seasons.
title: MS Dhoni has a word with Sanjiv Goenka after CSK win vs LSG

description: Paige Bueckers, fresh off a national championship with UConn, was drafted first overall by the Dallas Wings in the WNBA. Overwhelmed with gratitude, Bueckers expressed excitement about joining the Wings and exploring Dallas. Despite a challenging college career marked by an ACL injury, she emerged stronger, leading UConn to victory.
title: Bueckers shares heartfelt message after Dallas Wings select her No 1 in WNBA Draft

description: Ajith Kumar's action entertainer 'Good Bad Ugly' has stormed into the Rs 100 crore club within just five days of its release. The film's strong performance is driven by robust Tamil occupancy, particularly in Chennai and Madurai, while the Telugu version shows consistent, modest figures. Despite mixed reviews, the film is a celebration for Ajith fans, with callbacks to his older hits.
title: ‘Good Bad Ugly’ box office collections: Ajith’s action flick mints Rs 101.30 cr

description: Mehul Choksi, the fugitive businessman, owes approximately Rs 63 lakh in unpaid maintenance fees for his Malabar Hill flat in Mumbai, spanning over seven years. A society member reported that Choksi owns three units, including an illegally occupied terrace, and the outstanding amount could reach Rs 95 lakh with renovation costs.
title: Mehul Choksi owes Rs 63 lakh in maintenance dues for Mumbai flats: Report

description: MS Dhoni's vintage performance and humility shone as Chennai Super Kings defeated Lucknow Super Giants. Despite winning Player of the Match, Dhoni credited Noor Ahmad's exceptional bowling. Dhoni's unbeaten 26 off 11 balls secured the win, while young Shaik Rasheed's impressive 27 off 19 provided a strong foundation. Rasheed’s timing and shot selection caught the eye, with his stylish strokeplay showing maturity beyond his years. Dhoni, impressed by the youngster's composure, praised his ability to play “authentic shots.”
title: MS Dhoni's unexpected reaction: 'Why are they giving me the award?'

description: Sean "Diddy" Combs pleaded not guilty to new federal sex trafficking and prostitution charges, as prosecutors expand the racketeering case against him. Accused of abusing and coercing women for two decades, Combs faces five criminal counts. The trial is set for May 5, but a delay is possible due to new evidence. Combs has been incarcerated since September 2024.
title: Sean ‘Diddy’ Combs pleads not guilty to new sex trafficking, prostitution charges
Students, experts flag big errors in JEE Main papers

description: Motilal Oswal Financial Services recommends Indian Hotels and HPCL as top stock picks for the week starting April 14, 2025. IHCL's asset-light strategy and new segments are expected to drive growth, targeting a 26% adj. PAT CAGR.
title: Top stocks to buy: Stock recommendations for this week

description: The Trump administration has frozen $2.2 billion in grants and $6 million in contracts to Harvard University after the institution declined to comply with policy changes suggested by the US President. These changes included sharing hiring data and ensuring viewpoint diversity across academic departments.
title: Trump vs Harvard University: Full text of who said what

description: Blue Origin's New Shepard capsule soared to space. It carried an all-women crew, including Katy Perry and others. The sub-orbital flight reached over 100 kilometers. The crew experienced weightlessness before a smooth landing in West Texas. This mission marks a milestone for women in space exploration. The capsule soared at three times the speed of sound.
title: Watch: The moment Blue Origin rocket lands with Katy Perry and all-women crew

description: A new encounter started between security forces and terrorists in Poonch's Lasana village. The event occurred on Monday night. Security forces initiated a search operation after receiving information about terrorist presence. One Army personnel sustained injuries during the exchange of fire. The injured personnel was promptly taken to a hospital.
title: Fresh encounter breaks out in J&K's Poonch; 1 soldier injured

description: MS Dhoni's vintage performance led Chennai Super Kings to a thrilling five-wicket victory over Lucknow Super Giants in the IPL. Dhoni's unbeaten 26, along with Shivam Dube's 43*, secured the win, ending CSK's losing streak. It was Dhoni’s 16th Player of the Match award as captain, coming after a long gap of 2175 days — nearly six years.
title: MS Dhoni breaks 11-year-old IPL record in style

description: Harvard University is facing a $2.2 billion funding freeze after rejecting White House mandates to combat campus anti-Semitism. President Alan Garber refused to compromise Harvard's independence, leading to the grant suspension. This follows increased campus tensions and investigations into anti-Semitic incidents.
title: Trump admin freezes $2.2 bn in grants to Harvard after university defies its demands

description: Melinda French Gates addressed her 2021 divorce from Bill Gates, deeming it "necessary" due to conflicting values within their marriage. While Bill expressed regret over the split, Melinda focused on her own well-being and happiness. She also revealed experiencing panic attacks during the separation and finding solace in therapy. Currently single, she is embracing the dating scene.
title: Melinda Gates on Bill Gates’ statement that divorce was biggest regret

description: Palestinian student Mohsen Mahdawi, a Columbia University activist, was detained by immigration agents during his citizenship interview in Vermont. His arrest followed his vocal participation in anti-Israel protests, raising concerns about politically motivated targeting.
title: Palestinian student Mohsen Mahdawi arrested during citizenship interview

description: Aarthi Subramanian is poised to become TCS's first woman COO and the first woman C-suite executive at a major Indian IT firm, marking a significant milestone for gender diversity in the industry. Having served as the group chief digital officer at Tata Sons, she brings extensive experience and a deep understanding of TCS to her new role.
title: TCS's new COO Aarthi breaks IT glass ceiling

description: Dalal Street faces a truncated trading week influenced by tariff developments, US bond yields, FPI activity, and corporate earnings. Volatility is expected to persist despite potential easing in the US-China trade war. Investors will closely monitor Infosys, Wipro, HDFC Bank, and ICICI Bank results after TCS's underwhelming performance, alongside commodity market trends, particularly Goldman Sachs' revised gold price target.
title: What next? Dalal Street seeks direction amid tariff chaos

description: Erim Kaur, a London-based entrepreneur, has built a $4.2 million luxury haircare brand, ByErim, leveraging her large social media following. Inspired by her childhood and traditional Indian hair oiling practices learned from her grandmother after her mother's death, Kaur created a hair growth oil.
title: Indian-origin influencer builds $4M hair oil brand inspired by Indian traditions

description: Karnataka's government faces internal pressure following the leak of a caste census report. Vokkaliga and Lingayat leaders are contesting the population estimates, claiming higher numbers. Deputy CM DK Shivakumar convened a meeting with Vokkaliga legislators to address their concerns. The leaked report suggests a 10.
title: Lingayat, Vokkaliga netas huddle ahead of April 17 caste census meet

description: During a White House celebration honouring the Ohio State Buckeyes' national championship, vice president JD Vance accidentally toppled the trophy, causing a stir among the team and President Trump. Despite the mishap, Coach Ryan Day considered the visit an honor, marking a final celebration before key players depart for the NFL Draft, signaling a period of transition for the team.
title: Watch: JD Vance drops trophy, jokes ‘didn’t want anyone else to get it’

description: MLB announces Aaron Judge as Team USA Captain for the World Baseball Classic 2026. The announcement has led to mixed reviews from fans, with majority criticizing MLB's decision on choosing Judge as the captain when other capable players were still active. Meanwhile, fan war between Judge's fans and Ohtani's fans continue to happen on social media.
title: Why isn’t it Ohtani?: Fan war continues as Aaron Judge becomes US captain

description: Bootleggers in Gujarat attempted a novel smuggling operation by exploiting the Indian postal service to transport liquor from Diu. They believed using postal channels would evade police scrutiny at the Diu-Gujarat border. However, police intercepted a suspect carrying liquor-filled parcels with official postal stamps, revealing the involvement of a postmaster who facilitated the scheme.
title: Booze by mail? Now, postal service used to smuggle liquor into dry Gujarat
